ReturnPolicy.Description:
Unless seller error, Buyer is responsible for returning the merchandise and for all shipping expenses to return the item (no refund for the cost to send the item back will be given). 

• Shipping which is not free will not be refunded back, i.e. expedited, 2 day, etc. If you  pay for shipping unfortunately this is a non-refundable fee.
• For items sold by Luggage online the cost from shipping the item out may be deducted from your refund depending on the reason for return. 
• If you need a discounted prepaid label, please contact us by email. A discounted label will be provided and deducted from your refund. 

If the item is a seller error a prepaid shipping label may be offered and the item must be sent within the next 7 days after label is issued.  If the item is not sent back within the 7 days the label will be voided and the return request will need to be requested again.  After 30 days the return will be rejected. 

What to Do Next:

Once the item is authorized to be returned, print authorization information along with RMA information and include with return to help speed the processed of your item being returned and processed within Luggage Online’s warehouse. 

Additional Information:

• For international orders where the return was the result of our error and not exported using a freight forwarder, we'll reimburse you for the shipping costs after we receive it (if it's shipped using an economical method). 
• When using a freight forwarder you become the shipper and receiver and are responsible for returning all items back to the US regardless of the reason. A refund on shipping will not be given. 
• Items valued at over $75 must be returned to the seller with a trackable shipping service. If the order is valued at $100 or more, insure the shipment for the value of the merchandise and ship your return with a signature shipping service. For items below $75, we suggest USPS delivery confirmation service.
